{{Expand Estonian|Henri Laupmaa|date=November 2018}}
'''Henri Laupmaa''' (born 14 March 1975) is Estonian IT enerpreneur and board member of Estonian Fund for Nature.
He has studied international management in Concordia International University Estonia and Concordia University Wisconsin (BA, 1997) and graphics design in Estonian Art Academy.
Henri Laupmaa founded Let's Do It World a movement to clean up the world's environment of illegal trash<ref>Team and Board members Let's Do It. https://www.letsdoitworld.org/about/overview/3384-2/</ref> and has taken part of TEDx Tallinn conference organizing from its start in 2009.<ref name="tedxtallinn">{{cite web|url=http://www.tedxtallinn.ee/tedxtallinn-2009/|author=LUK Design Oy|title=TEDxTallinn 2009|website=TEDxTallinn|accessdate=2018-11-12}}</ref> Member of the Estonian President's Though Council from 2012 to 2016.
Founded the first creative crowdfunding platform in Estonia called Hooandja in 2012.
Founded the equity crowdfunding platform Fundwise in 2015.
